The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 The City Diary

 The bail petition of Prabhu Shankar Agarwal, the owner of Haldiram?s chain of confectioneries, was rejected on Wednesday. He was arrested by city police?s detective department on charges of engaging a professional killer to eliminate a Burrabazar-based tea-stall owner. The additional chief metropolitan magistrate rejected the petition filed by Agarwal?s lawyer. Agarwal, now lodged in Presidency jail, will be produced in court on June 30.

 Touhid Hossain, deputy high commissioner of Bangladesh in Calcutta, called on chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee on Wednesday morning. Hossain said that though law and order problems exist along the Indo-Bangla border, there has been no infiltration. Mohammad Imran, presently posted as deputy chief of mission, Ottowa, will soon succeed Hossain in Calcutta.

 The drivers of two trucks were killed when the vehicles collided on the Kona flyover, under Liluah police station, on Wednesday afternoon. Ersad, 30, and Sakaldwip Roy, 50, died on the spot. The truck Ersad was driving had an Andhra Pradesh registration number.

 Traders put up a roadblock for 40 minutes on Wednesday morning at the Nirmal Chandra Dey Street-Jadunath Dey Lane intersection to protest police inaction in curbing crime in the area. The protesters alleged that criminals extorting money from them were not being arrested. The blockade was lifted after senior police officers assured the traders that action would be taken against the extortionists.

 The first-ever Bengali translation in Braille of Story of My Life (on Helen Keller) will be released on Friday by the Blind Persons? Association. The association will observe Keller?s 125th birth anniversary on June 27. To mark the occasion, it will organise a seminar on Keller?s life on Friday at the auditorium in Dr HL Roy Building at Jadavpur University. 

 A 45-year-old man was seriously injured when a private bus on route 205A knocked him down on Lenin Sarani on Wednesday afternoon. According to police, Mantu Ghosh was crossing the road when the bus hit him from behind. The driver sped away with the bus. Ghosh was rushed to Calcutta Medical College and Hospital, where he is under observation.

 The BP Poddar group, which recently inaugurated a hospital near Hastings, will shortly come up with a series of day-care centres in the city under the aegis of the BP Poddar Clinic. The centres will provide state-of-the-art facilities in various branches of medicine. Arun Poddar, chairman of the BP Poddar group, will announce the project on Thursday.

 Five persons were injured when a bus carrying a marriage party was hit by a Matador on the Howrah-Amta Road, in Majhkshetra, under Jagatballavpur police station, on Wednesday. No one was arrested, but the vehicles were impounded.

 On the occasion of the 52nd Balidan Divas of Dr Shyama Prasad Mukherjee on Thursday, the Dr Shyama Prasad Mukherjee Smarak Samity will pay floral tributes at his memorial at Keoratala burning ghat at 8 am.

